episodes.title: President Trump says he never went to Jeffrey Epstein's island
episodes.description: President Donald Trump spoke with reporters on Monday after unveiling a new battleship class for the U.S. Navy. He was asked about the release of the Epstein Files, and says he's never been to Jeffrey Epstein's island.

episodes.title: Tom Lyden from the vault: Maidens of River Road
episodes.description:
In 2014, Tom Lyden exposed a cult leader in Pine County, Minnesota, that had been sexually abusing women and young girls. The cult leader, Victor Bernard, was eventually arrested in Brazil following an international man hunt.

episodes.title: Civil lawsuit filed aginst cult leader Victor Bernard's religious group
episodes.description: A woman who was sexually assaulted by cult leader Victor Barnard for nearly a decade, beginning when she was 13 years old, is now filing a civil lawsuit against 15 former leaders of his religious group, the River Road Fellowship.

episodes.title: Cult leader Victor Barnard pleads guilty
episodes.description: Cult leader Victor Barnard pleaded guilty to sexual assault charges  in Pine County, Minnesota. Barnard will spend 30 years in prison. Barnard pleaded guilty to two of 52 counts and agreed to upward departure. In court, Barnard said he wanted to spare the victims a trial
